remarks.format:
## Remarks

`SKWebpEncoder` provides static methods for encoding pixel data to WebP format, including both single-frame and animated WebP.

Use `Encode` to encode a single <xref:SkiaSharp.SKPixmap> to WebP, and `EncodeAnimated` to create an animated WebP from a sequence of <xref:SkiaSharp.SKWebpEncoderFrame> values.

## Examples

```csharp
// Encode a single image
using var bitmap = new SKBitmap(100, 100);
var data = SKWebpEncoder.Encode(bitmap.PeekPixels(), new SKWebpEncoderOptions(SKWebpEncoderCompression.Lossy, 80));

// Encode an animated WebP
var frames = new[]
{
    new SKWebpEncoderFrame(bitmap, TimeSpan.FromMilliseconds(100)),
    new SKWebpEncoderFrame(bitmap2, TimeSpan.FromMilliseconds(100))
};
var animData = SKWebpEncoder.EncodeAnimated(frames, new SKWebpEncoderOptions(SKWebpEncoderCompression.Lossless, 100));
```
